text: Wilby is a village and civil parish in the Mid Suffolk part of Suffolk in eastern England. It is around nine miles south-east of Diss, in 2001 there was 231 people living in Wilby. It has a primary school, village hall, Church, Trucking company (TG Askews) and a phone box (cards only). ==Transport== Between 1908 and 1952 the village had a railway station on the Mid-Suffolk Light Railway. == References == Category:Villages in Suffolk Category:Civil parishes in Suffolk
title: Wilby, Suffolk
